Frequently Asked Questions for Crh Plc (NYSE:CRH)
What is Crh Plc's stock symbol?

Crh Plc trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "CRH."



How often does Crh Plc pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for Crh Plc?

Crh Plc announced a semiannual dividend on Friday, March 3rd. Stockholders of record on Monday, March 13th will be given a dividend of $0.483 per share on Friday, May 12th. This represents a dividend yield of 2.77%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Thursday, March 9th. This is an increase from Crh Plc's previous semiannual dividend of $0.20.  View Crh Plc's Dividend History.



Who are some of Crh Plc's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Crh Plc include Vulcan Materials Company (VMC), Martin Marietta Materials (MLM), USG Corporation (USG), Summit Materials (SUM), Armstrong World Industries (AWI), GCP Applied Technologies (GCP), Marshalls plc (MSLH), Forterra (FRTA), Forterra PLC (FORT), Smart Sand (SND) and Fox Marble Holdings PLC (FOX).



Who are Crh Plc's key executives?

Crh Plc's management team includes the folowing people: Albert Manifold, Chief Executive Officer, Executive DirectorSenan Murphy, Finance Director, Executive DirectorMaeve Carton, Group Transformation Director, Executive DirectorNicky Hartery, Non-Executive Chairman of the BoardErnst J. Bartschi, Non-Executive DirectorPatrick J. Kennedy, Non-Executive DirectorDonald A. McGovern Jr., Senior Non-Executive Independent DirectorHeather Ann McSharry, Non-Executive Director



Who owns Crh Plc stock?

